[{"id":27690,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COOC}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5+\\mathrm{NaCl}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{Cl}+\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{COONa}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COCl}+\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{OH}+\\mathrm{NaOH}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COONa}+\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{OH}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":27655,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["Heating trans-but-2-enedioic acÄ±d","Heating cis-but-2-enedioic acid","Treating cis-but-2-enedioic acid with alcohol and acid","Treating trans-but-2-enedioic acid with alcohol and acid"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Heating cis-but-2-enedioic acid give maleic anhydride as follows,</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/03acca85-8093-4fe8-bf94-6d09d8a7fc90-image.png\" style=\"width: 505px; height: 265px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27664,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/af86db18-587a-43db-b04b-4107903d0f0d-image.png\" style=\"width: 280px; height: 81px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/01f3d623-a94d-41c1-b978-d8506b68cb74-image.png\" style=\"width: 280px; height: 80px;\" />","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>COOCH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>COOCH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msub></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7c9c48b6-6143-4221-bdeb-e1ba96e6e12e-image.png\" style=\"width: 774px; height: 192px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (03 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27622,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["$A>D>B>C$","$C>A>D>B$","$C>B>A>D$","$A>D>C>B$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Product [A]: From PhNH₂, steps (1) NaNO₂ + HCl forms diazonium salt, (2) CuCN gives benzonitrile, (3) H₃O⁺/Δ hydrolyzes to benzoic acid (PhCOOH), pKa ≈ 4.2.<br>Product [B]: From CH₃CH₂CHO, Tollens' oxidation with $[Ag(NH_3)_2]^+$ produces acetic acid (CH₃COOH), pKa ≈ 4.8.<br>Product [C]: From CH₄ + O₂ with heat and Na₂Cr₂O₇/H⁺ produces formic acid (HCOOH), pKa ≈ 3.8 (strongest acid).<br>Product [D]: From PhCH₂MgBr + CO₂, the Grignard reaction produces phenylacetic acid (PhCH₂COOH), pKa ≈ 4.3.<br>Acidic strength order (lower pKa = stronger): C (3.8) > A (4.2) > D (4.3) > B (4.8).","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (28 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27643,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1bf873c2-ea5c-4235-af37-d95927109697-image.png\" style=\"width: 346px; height: 70px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/94f580d1-c56f-4df0-9df5-9b7c80e4b7e4-image.png\" style=\"width: 352px; height: 90px;\" /></p>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2dda7458-854d-4202-9b7f-dbbe05b5ec08-image.png\" style=\"width: 361px; height: 90px;\" />","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f0b799e6-8b68-4dc0-9bc9-d3eec561a68b-image.png\" style=\"width: 316px; height: 60px;\" /></p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>DiBAL-H is&nbsp;Diisobutylaluminium hydride, which is a very useful reducing agent. It is used for selectively converting ester or nitriles into respective aldehydes. It does not affect other groups like aldehyde or double bond.&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4ef7aab7-f5fc-4422-8d02-76f9e36b3c9a-dec4377f-1cd8-4a10-ae36-907c1a68790d-image.png\" style=\"width: 396px; height: 231px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27688,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COOH}$","$\\mathrm{HCOOH}$","$\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_3\\right)_2 \\mathrm{COOH}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{COOH}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":27645,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["alkylated product with ortho and para&nbsp;substitution.","secondary amine after acidic treatment.","an amide product.","positively charged nitrogen at benzene ring."],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Aniline does not undergo Friedel-crafts reaction&nbsp;due to salt formation with aluminium chloride, the Lewis acid, which is used as a catalyst, whereas&nbsp;aniline is a strong base. So, an acid-base reaction will take place. Thus, aniline reacts with <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></math> to form a salt.<br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/75d7b7ac-4e45-493a-91c6-85fa0ddc3273-9711822.png\" style=\"width: 270px; height: 157px;\" /><br />Due to the positive charge on the nitrogen atom (shows <math><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> effect and it is meta directing), electrophilic substitution in the benzene ring is deactivated. Hence, the Friedel-Crafts reaction will not take place in aniline.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27635,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/14d9c468-f21c-42de-9220-a2b609f24fed.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 156px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c7b403d1-ddae-4a9e-aaf5-f70d86a78d4d.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 111px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e6884dcf-f016-4c6b-9661-bcc32ecda062.png\" style=\"width: 249px; height: 240px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/08ee4d77-5310-4c7c-b87a-ef73d15176c8.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 138px;\"/>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><strong>Freidel-Crafts Acylation:</strong></p><ul> <li>Friedel-Crafts acylation reaction is a type of reaction where an acyl group is added to an aromatic ring.</li> <li>This reaction occurs in the presence of an acid chloride <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>Cl</mi></math> and a Lewis acid catalyst like Aluminium chloride <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>AlCl</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>.</li> <li>Friedel-Crafts acylation reaction, changes the aromatic ring into a aromatic ketone.<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/de8f3d55-e97a-44e6-8539-3bf23280d899.png\" style=\"width: 704px; height: 521px;\"/></li></ul>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27692,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CHO}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{COOH}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{LiAl}^{\\mathrm{H}}{ }_4$ can reduce $\\mathrm{COOH}$ group and not the double bond\n$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{COOH} \\underset{\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}}{\\stackrel{\\mathrm{LAH}}{\\longrightarrow}}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":27666,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/455e3256-1b86-4c4e-ad2e-0c35ccaa5e32-image.png\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 143px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/22ef2827-4694-48b2-b97c-d3371d134f9d-image.png\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 137px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5b18e806-d439-4a4c-a52b-664bc2ad36e8-image.png\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 152px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dab77aca-7b17-4549-8df1-d9078650224a-image.png\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 164px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Chromium oxide is an oxidising&nbsp;agent and oxidizes alcohol to carboxylic&nbsp;acid, which on reaction with thionyl chloride convert into acyl halide followed by hydrolysis.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/83aee770-f149-4400-a915-d73c4361a9ce-080818d1-1cbf-4708-9a2b-3a078e04e876-image.png\" style=\"width: 502px; height: 487px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27661,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>OH</mi><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><mrow><msub><mi>CrO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>SO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></mrow></mover></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mfrac><mrow><mi>Pd</mi><mfenced><mi>II</mi></mfenced><mo>/</mo><mi>Cu</mi><mfenced><mi>II</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>CN</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>)&#160;</mo><mi>DIBAL</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>ii</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>)</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#62;</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>OH</mi><mfrac><mi>Cu</mi><mrow><mn>573</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#62;</mo></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Ethyl alcohol on oxidation with acidified chromium oxide forms acetic acid. The reaction is as follows:</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/869e492d-5793-4fe3-bdc2-72e1f8527665-image.png\" style=\"width: 420px; height: 159px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27636,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5a60e685-6dd7-4661-b430-0a8d5f8da08e.png\" style=\"width: 800px; height: 149px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5760d412-4ce2-4321-9c56-5a17da992a89.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 163px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/43e14125-985a-41d6-96f7-d05813970d5f.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 162px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a56cfc97-addf-48d2-9080-bc3762d93757.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 169px;\"/>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Reaction of aniline sulphonic acid with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NaNO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi></math> gives diazo ester sulphonic acid. Which on further treatment with naphthalene derivative undergoes diazo coupling reaction to give red azo dye.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4794da58-c530-4672-ad6a-6a7ebfa24171.png\" style=\"width: 700px; height: 270px;\"/></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2cca182a-c4db-4896-828d-ccf85b1c2e1e.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 530px;\"/></p><p>This is known as Griess-Ilosvay test. </p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27641,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>The&nbsp;trisubstituted compound &#39;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>&#39;, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>12</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;gives neutral <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>FeCl</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;test positive, means the compound is phenol. Phenol on&nbsp;treatment with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>NaOH</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>Br</mi></math> gives <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>11</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>. The given&nbsp;compound is reacting with hot conc. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>NaOH</mi></math> gives a compound <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>12</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>. The reaction is Cannizzaro&#39;s reaction. Hence, compound must be&nbsp;benzaldehyde derivative. Compound &#39;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>&#39; also decolourises alkaline <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>KMnO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>, means compound contains an alkyl group attached to benzene ring. Hence, the structure of the compound can be written as follows,</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bbeffd61-56c1-4021-9be7-c9e485b6310c-image.png\" style=\"width: 236px; height: 222px;\" /></p><p>The reactions are shown below.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d4e638fa-0ba1-4d68-b78d-78eb3598acb6-image.png\" style=\"width: 441px; height: 169px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/32fc7843-aab9-4637-8c93-33413037faf0-image.png\" style=\"width: 656px; height: 175px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0a84fd7d-e596-4a39-b4d2-602f88beebd9-image.png\" style=\"width: 493px; height: 165px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27662,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4ef1274b-bc04-4d37-abe6-b5c37edce7ad-image.png\" style=\"width: 127px; height: 89px;\" /></p>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9ef72861-a33d-40c7-98c6-eb7ba4414b8f-image.png\" style=\"width: 157px; height: 78px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7a3e9f6a-ac83-42fd-b27a-b9009f5f7e8d-image.png\" style=\"width: 132px; height: 92px;\" />","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>RO</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>CMe</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"Esters are hydrolysed in basic medium(saponification)","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (05 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27634,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img s